meta {
  name: Search Documents
  type: http
  seq: 1
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/search
  body: json
  auth: none
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/json
}

body:json {
  {
    "query": "How does the system decide chunk size for ingestion?",
    "top_k": 5
  }
}

docs {
  ## Search Documents

  Embeds `query` with the configured `EmbeddingProvider`, then returns the
  `top_k` most similar chunks from the `embeddings` table by cosine
  similarity. No LLM generation, similarity threshold fallback, or citation
  checking is applied here — see `Ask/Ask Question` for the full RAG flow.

  ### Request body

  | Field    | Type   | Required | Default | Description                                |
  |----------|--------|----------|---------|----------------------------------------------|
  | `query`  | string | yes      | —       | Natural-language search query.                |
  | `top_k`  | int    | no       | `5`     | Number of results to return.                  |

  ### Response `200`

  ```json
  {
    "results": [
      {
        "id": 1,
        "text_chunk": "Archon is a retrieval-augmented generation system...",
        "document_id": "doc-architecture-overview",
        "similarity_score": 0.83
      }
    ]
  }
  ```

  | Field                       | Type   | Description                                  |
  |------------------------------|--------|-------------------------------------------------|
  | `results[].id`               | int    | Row id in `embeddings`.                          |
  | `results[].text_chunk`       | string | The stored chunk text.                           |
  | `results[].document_id`      | string | Document the chunk belongs to.                   |
  | `results[].similarity_score` | float  | Cosine similarity to the query (higher = closer).|
}
